From 6613e915290c3c88a3f7fae361d6c6fda49182f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Sep 2025 13:58:08 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:PROTOCOL:Hostapd: Delete station while skipping kernel
 delete

When a legacy STA roams from one link to another within the same MLD,
hostapd will show a non-active (stale) entry for about 300 seconds in
the initial associated link. There is no functional impact on
connectivity or traffic on the roamed link; this is only a temporary
visibility issue. But, skip_kernel_delete flag is present inorder to
avoid sending delete command to kernel/driver in the roamed link. Hence,
keeping the stale entry in hostapd is of no use.

Delete the stale entry by immediately freeing the sta in the inactive
link without waiting for inactive timer expiry.

Signed-off-by: Manish Dharanenthiran <mdharane@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 src/ap/utils.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/src/ap/utils.c
+++ b/src/ap/utils.c
@@ -77,8 +77,14 @@ static int prune_associations(struct hos
 		if (data->mld_assoc_link_id >= 0 &&
 		    osta->mld_assoc_link_id == data->mld_assoc_link_id)
 			continue;
-		if (skip_prune_for_partner_links(data->hapd, osta))
+		if (skip_prune_for_partner_links(data->hapd, osta)) {
+			/* Delete the sta instead of waiting for inactivity
+			 * timer
+			 */
+			if (osta->skip_kernel_delete)
+				ap_free_sta(ohapd, osta);
 			continue;
+		}
 #endif /* CONFIG_IEEE80211BE */
 
 		wpa_printf(MSG_INFO, "%s: Prune association for " MACSTR,
